---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../consts';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | Questling';
const description =
  'Questling has no accounts and no servers. Everything the app saves stays on your phone. Nothing is collected, tracked, sold, or shared.';

// The date the policy was last actually changed (not auto-updated).
const lastUpdated = 'June 30, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        I'm the developer of Questling, and I made it so your stuff stays with you.
        The app has no accounts and no servers behind it, so nothing it saves ever
        leaves your phone.
      </p>

      <h2>What's kept on your phone</h2>
      <p>While you use the app, it remembers a few things, all stored on your own device:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>your gems, the quests you've finished, and the quest you're currently on</li>
        <li>the rewards you add in the Shop</li>
        <li>any photos you attach in the Memory Journal</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I never see any of it. There's nowhere for the app to send it, so it doesn't.</p>

      <h2>Camera and photos</h2>
      <p>
        Questling only asks for your camera or photos so you can save a picture with a
        quest as a keepsake. Those pictures stay on your phone and aren't uploaded anywhere.
      </p>

      <h2>What I collect</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing. No tracking, no analytics, no ads, no accounts. I don't collect, sell,
        or share any of your information, and nobody else does either, because none of it
        leaves your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
      <p>
        You can remove individual photos and rewards right in the app. If you want all of
        it gone, deleting the app takes everything with it.
      </p>

      <h2>Kids</h2>
      <p>
        Questling is meant for a parent to run on their own phone. Since nothing is
        collected and nothing leaves the device, no personal information is gathered from
        anyone, kids included.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>If I change this policy, I'll update the date at the top.</p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>Email me at <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container--narrow { max-width: 720px; }
  h1 { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .updated { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 2.2rem; }
  p, li { color: var(--ink); }
  ul { margin: 0 0 1.1rem; padding-left: 1.3rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  a { color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
